list.name: Default
list.comment: Done with restructuring for MV-RNN. Reproduces results for the logic toy example in Socher's "Semantic Compositionality through Recursive Matrix-Vector Spaces". Backprop should now match his exactly. The zero percent error rate is dependent upon the nonlinearity, and thus shouldn't be anticipated for real applications.

task.summary: Added MV-RNN functionality. Compositionality of logical operators seems to work as expected, tested using word dimensions of one and two. Less than one percent difference between network outputs and training targets for that task. MvRnnTree contains the compositionality methods.
Consolidated MV-RNN training parameters into a single configuration file and object.

In most recent implementation, backprop is done on the tree recursively. At each each node, forward prop is done on that node prior to calxulating error and updating weights. Thus for a full update of the tree, the forward algorithm is run many times. This is not how backprop is described in the MV-RNN paper, and will be changed in a future update.

Backprop for MV-RNN is closer to the method described in the Socher's Semantic Compositionality through Recursive Matrix-Vector Spaces. However, updates still take place earlier than they should. Future structural changes should fix this. Randomly initialized values are now smaller and positive, to replicate Socher's toy problem, composition of logical functions. Results were replicated successfully.
